  "summary": "The paper proposes Data-Efficient FineTuning (DEFT), a method that selects relevant subsets from a large multitask data pool (P3) by retrieving \"cross-task nearest neighbors\" using a small number of unlabeled target task instances. DEFT aims to outperform training on entire multitask datasets by mitigating negative interference and improving data efficiency. Experiments show DEFT models, trained on significantly less data, consistently outperform a strong T0-3B baseline in both zero-shot and few-shot settings.",
